description:
Foundation for .tldr/config.json. Add serde structs in tldr-core (or tldr-cli):
  TldrConfig { version:u32, embedding: EmbeddingConfig, semantic: SemanticConfig }
  EmbeddingConfig { provider: String (default "local"), model: Option<String>, endpoint: Option<String>, api_key_env: Option<String>, dimensions: Option<usize> }
  SemanticConfig { enabled: bool (default true), langs: Option<Vec<String>> }
Rules: #[serde(default)] on every field; do NOT use deny_unknown_fields (ignore unknown keys for forward-compat). Add serde_json (already present) — no new TOML dep needed since format is JSON. Provide a from_str + from_path (returns default on missing file). Unit tests: empty {}, partial, unknown-keys-ignored, full cloud-shaped block parses.

comments.text:
SPEC ADDITION (2026-06-06, user-ratified): LAYER TAXONOMY — the derivation rule for the cache stack (frames the segment model; intended opening section of the consolidation doc).
RULE: a layer exists IFF it has a DISTINCT INVALIDATION TRIGGER and lifetime. One trigger per layer, one layer per trigger. Fewer = merged lifetimes (the ADR-9 'misfiled lifetimes' sin); more = fragments with no trigger to bind to.
L0 GROUND TRUTH: source files. Not a cache. Trigger: user edits.
L1 SYNTAX: parse trees (S1). Key: file content hash. Trigger: THIS file's bytes. Survives: all other files' edits.
L2 FACTS (project-blind): per-function bundles/metric rows/fingerprints/embeddings (S2, body+env hash) + per-file compose-input facts (S3, file hash). Trigger: THIS function's body or THIS file's env. Survives: sibling edits, line shifts above, other files. Two grains, ONE layer (same trigger class).
L3 RESIDENT STRUCTURES: CSR snapshot + indexes (S4), BM25 postings (S6). Generationed. Trigger: any compose-input change -> O(V+E) rebuild CONSUMING WARM L2 (rebuild cheap BECAUSE L2 is warm).
L4 DERIVED ARTIFACTS: pagerank/betweenness/SCC/clones/coupling/aggregates (S5). Key: slice hash via pinned-generation lookup. Trigger: ITS OWN slice changing. Survives rebuilds with unchanged slice.
L5 PERSISTENCE: on-disk CAS backing L2 (T3). Trigger: GC sweep only. Survives: PROCESS RESTART (the trigger no RAM layer survives).
SIDE LANE (outside the stack, deliberate): external truth (S7 churn/diagnostics/coverage/doctor/fix) keyed by git HEAD/tool versions, never daemon-resident — its trigger (the outside world) is not ours to track; caching it would manufacture staleness.
SANITY CHECK BOTH DIRECTIONS: merging L2 into L3 re-derives today's disease (every edit kills all per-function facts); splitting L2 (bundles vs metrics) adds a boundary with NO new trigger.
ANTICIPATED BENEFITS (claims subject to TLDR-rfz measurement + Codex review on TLDR-5qm):
(1) one-file edit: ~4ms reparse + only-changed L2 + ms L3 rebuild from warm L2 + mostly-surviving L4 — vs today's blunt language-bucket clear -> ~3s full rebuild repayment;
(2) comment/format-only edits: near-zero invalidation (edits above a function: zero via position-relative storage; edits inside a body: one function's L2 entries, no L3 rebuild since compose-input hashes unchanged);
(3) cross-command reuse: 15+ graph commands share L3; metric family shares one L2 fact set; agent sequences hit warm bundles — vs search rebuilding BM25+graph EVERY query today;
(4) coherence bug classes (jsi, daemon-vs-local drift) unexpressible under one contract;
(5) warm restarts via L5;
(6) every cache miss has a stated reason (provenance);
(7) cost MODEL change: pay per change, per layer, once — each layer's recompute made cheap by warmth of the layer below.
